this was done by me with by following bash command:
$ find new/ -type f | while read -r NEWFILE; do HASH=`cat "$NEWFILE" | sha512sum - | cut -d ' ' -f 1`; HASHC01=`echo $HASH | cut -c 1`; HASHC02=`echo $HASH | cut -c 2`; mv -v "$NEWFILE" $HASHC01/$HASHC02/$HASH; done 


why "storey"?
i am not very good in names giving, and that is what i came up with
